				\begin{document}$${I}_{ph}= {I}_{light}- {I}_{dark}$$\end{document}
where Idark is the dark current and Ilight is the current under illumination. The responsivity, R denotes the device sensitivity of incident light and is describes as the ratio of photocurrent generated to illuminated optical power intensity and calculated as Eq. (2):2R=IphPopt·A\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
